{"questionId":"22816","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The admissions team at a new university are trying to predict the number of student&nbsp;applications they will receive each year.</p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> be the number of years that the university has been open. The admissions team collect the following data for the first two years.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/0d0fd473258347545caf6a7a1bfc24be107809cc.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the percentage increase in applications from the first year to the second year.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo> </mo><mn>669</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mo> </mo><mn>300</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo> </mo><mn>300</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>100</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>%</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22816","referenceCode":"21N.2.SL.TZ0.2a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the percentage increase in applications from the first year to the second year.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.3—Geometric sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Approximating and estimating"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}